:R-HSA-379401  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The human gene SLC6A3 encodes the sodium-dependent dopamine transporter, DAT which mediates the re-uptake of dopamine from the synaptic cleft (Gu et al., 1994; Vandenbergh DJ et al, 2000). Dopamine can then be degraded by either COMT or monoamine oxidase." ;
        rdfs:label          "Clearance of dopamine" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Mahajan, SS, 2008-01-14 16:01:52" , "Edited: Mahajan, SS, 2008-11-18 00:03:09" , "Reviewed: Restituito, S, 2008-11-27 12:38:49" ;
